In Java 8, the Supplier<T> interface is a functional interface that represents a supplier of results.
Unlike Consumer or Function, it takes no input and returns a value of type T.

ğŸ”¹ Supplier Interface â€“ Definition
@FunctionalInterface
public interface Supplier<T> {
    T get();
}

T â€“ Type of the result
get() â€“ Returns a result of type T
No input parameters

âœ… When to Use Supplier<T>
To generate or fetch values lazily
To delay execution until needed
For random generation, object creation, or default value supply

âœ… Example 1: Supply a string
import java.util.function.Supplier;
public class SupplierExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Supplier<String> supplyHello = () -> "Hello from Supplier!";
        System.out.println(supplyHello.get());
    }
}

âœ… Example 2: Generate random numbers
import java.util.function.Supplier;
import java.util.Random;
public class RandomSupplier {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Supplier<Integer> randomSupplier = () -> new Random().nextInt(100); // 0 to 99

        for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
            System.out.println(randomSupplier.get());
        }
    }
}

âœ… Example 3: Lazy object initialization
import java.util.function.Supplier;
class ExpensiveObject {
    public ExpensiveObject() {
        System.out.println("Object created!");
    }

    public String toString() {
        return "Iâ€™m heavy to create!";
    }
}

public class LazyInitExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Supplier<ExpensiveObject> objectSupplier = () -> new ExpensiveObject();

        System.out.println("Before calling get()");
        ExpensiveObject obj = objectSupplier.get(); // Lazy init here
        System.out.println("After calling get(): " + obj);
    }
}

ğŸ”¹ Summary Table
| Feature           | Description                  |
| ----------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Interface         | `Supplier<T>`                |
| Functional Method | `T get()`                    |
| Input             | None                         |
| Output            | Returns a value of type T    |
| Use Case          | Lazy loading, default values |


ğŸ”¸ Comparison with Others
| Interface   | Input | Output | Use Case                        |
| ----------- | ----- | ------ | ------------------------------- |
| `Function`  | âœ…     | âœ…      | Transforming values             |
| `Predicate` | âœ…     | âœ…      | Testing conditions              |
| `Consumer`  | âœ…     | âŒ      | Consuming values (side-effects) |
| `Supplier`  | âŒ     | âœ…      | Supplying/generating values     |
